<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Submission first, then rehearsal — the dossier is done, but the defense is the part that proves you own the work.</p>
  <p>Your <a href="/units/unit-0/assessment-source-dossier/">Source Dossier</a> is due in the first 15 minutes today (written, or the video alternative). The rest of the block is rehearsal — paired peer-talk where each of you takes a turn defending your dossier while the other plays panelist. Twice. Then a 30-second whole-class share of your strongest pitch.</p>
  <p>Rehearsal isn't optional. The first defense you give tomorrow has to be at least your second defense, not your first. Make your mistakes today, with one partner, so you don't make them tomorrow in front of the panel. Your partner today is doing you a favor.</p>
  <figure class="content-figure">
    <img src="/assets/img/u0/u0-five-moves.svg" alt="Five-step strip for answering questions under pressure: one, acknowledge — take the question seriously; two, restate — say it back in your own words; three, answer — one claim, not a speech; four, cite — name the evidence it stands on; five, check — does that answer it.">
    <figcaption>The pattern you'll rehearse today and use in every defense this year.</figcaption>
  </figure>
</section>

